[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

Data by country, area, or territory for 1 Oct 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesOct1_1601607339.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 38.1% of daily case numbers and 54.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, maintaining its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 16.6 million cases. The USA and Brazil remain dominant, followed by Argentina, Colombia, Mexico, and Peru. Other countries reporting more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours include Chile, Canada, and Ecuador.

- The European region reported 21.6% of daily case numbers and 12.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 5.9 million. Countries not reporting cases today (1 Oct 2020) include Israel and Kazakhstan. The dominant country is France, followed by Russia, the UK, Ukraine, Spain, Netherlands, Germany, and Romania. Other countries reporting more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours include Italy, Poland, Turkey, Belgium, Austria, Czech Republic, Republic of Moldova.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.3% of daily case numbers and 5.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of greater than 2.4 million cases. Countries not reporting cases in the past 24 hours include Pakistan, Morocco, Egypt, Oman, UAE, Bahrain, Afghanistan, Lebanon, Tunisia, Sudan, Somalia, and Yemen. Iraq remains the dominant country, followed by Iran, Jordan, Kuwait, and Palestinian Authority.

- The African region reported 1.5% of daily case numbers and 1.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.1 million cases. South Africa is again the dominant country, followed by Ethiopia, Nigeria, Mozambique, Ghana, Algeria, Kenya, Namibia, Cabo Verde, Uganda, and Reunion. However, all reporting countries outside of South Africa reported less than 1000 cases.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.2% of daily case numbers and 1.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.61 million cases. The Philippines continues to dominate, followed by Japan, French Polynesia, Malaysia, and South Korea.

- The South East Asia region reported 33.3% of the daily newly reported cases and 24.5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.0 million cases. India continues to dominate followed by Indonesia, Nepal, Bangladesh, and Myanmar.

Today's report from the Eastern Mediterranean has the majority of countries not reporting any new cases in the past 24 hours. Europe is experiencing resurgences in many countries related to loosening restrictions and the summer vacation period. The Americas continue to have more countries reporting cases. Major transmission is also ongoing in South East Asia, specifically India, but other countries are following suit. - Cases are increasing in Nepal and Myanmar.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 1 Oct 2020 is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.MPP]

