[The USA, India, and Brazil are still the most severely affected countries in terms of cumulative case counts and daily new case confirmations, with India in the 2nd position followed by Brazil. In the past 24 hours, these 3 countries -- India (83 801), followed by the USA (47 389) and Brazil (35 643) -- account for over half (54.3%) of all confirmed cases globally and 50.4% of all newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. As the daily reports from each of the 3 countries have been dropping, other countries are reporting more newly confirmed cases. A global total of 8922 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (1-2 Oct 2020).

Countries reporting more than 5000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (12 countries) include India, USA, Brazil, Argentina (14 001), France (13 970), Israel (10 277), Spain (9419), Russia (8945), UK (6914), Colombia (5660), the Czech Republic (5336), and Mexico (5099); 42 countries have reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours. 14 of the 42 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region and 13 were from the Americas region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, there is an increase in case counts by 0.36%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 7.1%.

Impression: While the global 7-day averages appear to have plateaued, when one looks at the country-by-country figures, the 3 major countries -- the USA, India, and Brazil -- have decreased their daily newly confirmed cases, but other countries have increased transmission, especially in Europe and elsewhere in the Americas. - Mod.MPP]
